{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-item-template-js","path":"/models/mics/87-cond","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h4>Description</h4>\n<p>The U 87 was designed as a solid-state version of the U 67 tube microphone. It retained the K67-style capsule of the U67, but replaced the tube amplifier circuit with a FET/transformer design. In short, the U87 was a tripolar FET condenser with a transformer-coupled output. A switch below the headbasket allowed selection of Cardioid, Omni, or Figure-8 patterns.</p>","frontmatter":{"brand":"Neumann","instrument":null,"config":null,"channel":null,"path":"/models/mics/87-cond","model":"U87","url":"http://recordinghacks.com/microphones/Neumann/U-87","name":"87 Cond","type":["Condenser"],"update":["1.0"],"image":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"tracedSVG":"data:image/svg+xml,%3csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20width='400'%20height='129'%20viewBox='0%200%20400%20129'%20preserveAspectRatio='none'%3e%3cpath%20d='M334%2016a623%20623%200%2001-82%201A3305%203305%200%200152%2028l-11%207c-10%205-11%206-12%2010l-4%205c-4%201-7%2016-3%2018v4c-2%202%200%208%203%208l3%202c2%207%203%208%2013%2013l12%207a808%20808%200%200155%202%2014057%2014057%200%2000266%207h1l1-1v-2h1c1%201%201%201%201-1V82a160%20160%200%20011-28V37c1-1-1-12-3-16-3-5-6-6-23-6l-19%201m-71%2017l-1%2021c0%2015%200%2018-3%2016-1-1-1-1-1%201s-1%202-5%202c-5%200-6%200-6-2l-2-1-2%201v10c0%2011-1%2010%207%2011a9693%209693%200%200112%202%20397%20397%200%20001-61m-48%2040a1458%201458%200%2001-104%203l-2%201c0%201-1%201-1-1h-3l-5%201-3%201-1%202c0%202%203%202%204%200h1c0%202%201%202%202%202h15l6%201h7l2%201h1l6-1%205%201h13l9%201h8l2%201h1a75%2075%200%200123%201%20399%20399%200%200033%202V74l-19-1'%20fill='%23d3d3d3'%20fill-rule='evenodd'/%3e%3c/svg%3e","aspectRatio":3.106194690265487,"src":"/static/f7261b14ae974a307efb72d70b526813/a9a3e/87-cond.png","srcSet":"/static/f7261b14ae974a307efb72d70b526813/3ec60/87-cond.png 351w,\n/static/f7261b14ae974a307efb72d